The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Tiruchirappalli, March 28: Toyota-Kirloskar Motor Pvt Ltd may enter the small car segment by 2010, a company official said. The company will also expand its dealers? network to 60 by the middle of this year from 55. It enjoys a 20 per cent share in the country?s premium and luxury car segments. Its utility vehicle, the Innova, has captured a 32 per cent market share, while the Corolla has achieved a 35 per cent share. 

 Mumbai, March 28: Reliance Natural Resources Ltd will raise Rs 1,100 crore through issue of shares on a preferential basis at a price not less than Rs 25.65. It has convened an extraordinary general meeting of shareholders on April 14 to consider the issue, the company has informed the BSE.

 Mumbai, March 28: The board of Hindustan Dorr Oliver Ltd has decided to split the equity shares of the company in 1:5 ratio, that is every share of Rs 10 will be split into five shares of Rs 2 each, the company informed the BSE.

 New Delhi, March 28: Prime Minister Manmohan Singh today reviewed the implementation of six projects under the ambitious Bharat Nirman programme that envisages building rural infrastructure.

 Mumbai, March 28: Bombay High Court has deferred till April 20 the hearing of petition filed by National Thermal Power Corporation against Reliance Industries Ltd for specific performance of gas sales and purchase agreement.

 New Delhi, March 28: The impact of information technology is far greater in rural areas than in cities, says a survey on e-governance project by ICT consultancy firm Skoch. The survey was conducted over the period of two years covering 37 e-governance projects.

 Mumbai, March 28: Oracle Global Ltd has acquired a 4.5 per cent stake in i-flex Solutions Ltd from open market purchases through Oracle Global Mauritius, taking its total stake in the company to 47.5 per cent.




